  "texts": [
    "WaveNet advances the output by several timestamps.",
    "As a result, that output lines up with the final input element [40].",
    "In comparison to innovative autoregressive models, flow-based models are conceptually promising for modeling complicated distributions but are constrained by performance concerns with density estimation.",
    "In addition, although flow models initially appear to be able to replace GANs in terms of providing respectable output, there is a considerable difference in the computational cost of training between them, with flow-based models requiring a lot more time than GANs to produce images with the same resolution.",
    "As a result, each algorithm (GAN, VAE, Flow-based Models) has advantages and disadvantages in terms of efficiency and accuracy."
